whatpulse (2.3-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New upstream release
    + Fix remaining client crashes
    + Allow GeoIP downloads on computers using non-standard charsets
    + Improve CPU usage by 20% and memory usage by 40%
    + Smoother update of the geek window
    + Ignore dead center clicks in the mouse heat map
    + If pulse on double click is disabled, open the main window on double click
  * Switch back to Debian-specific tarballs, as those also work on Wheezy

 -- Oxan van Leeuwen <oxan@oxanvanleeuwen.nl>  Sun, 08 Dec 2013 21:28:15 +0100

whatpulse (2.3~b1-1) experimental; urgency=low

  * New upstream release
    + Support for dvorak and azerty keyboard layouts in the heat map
    + Pulse new applications more often (when enabled)
    + Reduce amount of background workers (should reduce crashes)
    + Optimize bandwidth collector (improve performance in high-bandwidth cases)
    + Remove memory leak when disabling and re-enabling statistics manually
    + Fix crash on client exit
    + Fix incorrect counting of bandwidth (missing a few bytes)
    + Fix empty process details on some systems
  * Extract "normal" Linux tarballs, as these seem to work on Debian too now

 -- Oxan van Leeuwen <oxan@oxanvanleeuwen.nl>  Sun, 17 Nov 2013 17:33:16 +0100

whatpulse (2.2.1-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New upstream release
  * Add libx11-6 to Build-Depends
  * Fix removal of capabilities on first run of postinst script, when the binary
    doesn't have any capabilities.
  * Don't remove and recreate input group on every upgrade.
  * Install desktop file in correct directory
  * Add dependency on libssl-dev, because it loads the libcrypto.so library 
    (without a SONAME in the filename).

 -- Oxan van Leeuwen <oxan@oxanvanleeuwen.nl>  Tue, 29 Oct 2013 22:48:38 +0100

